<P><H1 align=center>PAYMENT PROTECTION DETAILS – CM040</H1>
<P></P>
<P><FONT color=red><STRONG>NOTE: </STRONG>areas shown in red are mandatory and must be completed to 
proceed</FONT>           </P>
<P><H3>Split cover: </H3>
<P>If it is a single application, this field will be greyed out, so defaulting 
to ‘No’.</P>
<P>If it is a joint application, select either the ‘Yes’ or ‘No’ radio 
buttons.</P>
<P></P>
<P><H3>Product: </H3>this is a drop-down field showing a list 
of products.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Product Options: </H3>this is a drop-down field showing 
a list of cover types available for the product.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Mortgage Cover: </H3>
<P>the applicant can select the amount of cover required, however the field 
below shows the ‘recommended mortgage cover amount’, which is the equivalent of 
the monthly mortgage payment.</P>
<P>If the cover is to be split between joint applicants, enter the amount 
required for each applicant. If it is a single applicant, these fields will be 
greyed out and the entire amount will be automatically entered in the field 
‘Mortgage Cover for Applicant 1’.</P>
<P></P>
<P><H3>Calculate: </H3>click on ‘Calculate’ and the premium 
will appear in ‘Monthly Cost’, based on the amount of cover required, the 
product and the product option.
<P></P>
<P><H3>View Sub-Quotes: </H3>clicking on ‘View Sub-Quotes’ will bring up the screen <A href="HELP_CM075.asp">CM075 
(View Sub-Quotes)</A>. This shows a list of 
the various quotes provided, and previous quotes can be reactivated by clicking 
the ‘Reinstate’ button.
<P></P>
<P>Click ‘<STRONG>OK</STRONG> ’ to return to the main Payment Protection screen.</P>
<P><H3>New Sub-Quote: </H3>clicking on this button will clear 
the quote calculated, and allows the information to be changed. Any previous 
quotes will be saved and can be viewed by clicking on ‘View Sub-Quotes’.
<P></P>
<P>Clicking on ‘OK’ leads back to <A href="HELP_CM010.asp">CM010 – Cost Modelling Menu</A></P>

